Instructions :
Run 'make' inside the project directory, for making the executable named 'transformer'

References :
Used the official documentation (www,glfw.org) of GLFW for reference for GLFW
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15242507/perspective-correct-texturing-of-trapezoid-in-opengl-es-2-0
http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~lizhang/courses/cs559-2010s/syllabus/03-15-hopman/lighting-texture.pdf
Code for reading bytes from a bmp file 
http://www.opengl-tutorial.org/beginners-tutorials/tutorial-5-a-textured-cube/
http://opengl.czweb.org/ch09/293-296.html


Keys :
Press Shift, Ctrl, Alt along with E, C, R, T, B, Y, N, U, I, ',', Q to move various parts of the bot. Use space bar to transform the bot. Use X, . to toggle head lights. Use W, E to toggle global lights. Use W to switch camera modes. And Esc to close window
